# Overview

This problem asks us to calculate the percentage of days on which "you" wash the dishes based on a system where you wash on day D if there exists an index i such that D mod M[i] <= R[i].

The key insight is that this pattern repeats with a period equal to the LCM (Least Common Multiple) of all M[i] values. We can simulate the pattern for one complete cycle and calculate the percentage.

The algorithm:
1. Read N, array M, and array R
2. Calculate the LCM of all values in M (this is the period)
3. For each day from 0 to LCM-1, check if any condition D mod M[i] <= R[i] is satisfied
4. Count how many days satisfy the condition
5. Return the percentage: (count / LCM) * 100

